BAMAKO - Two peacekeepers were killed and a third wounded on Tuesday in an ambush in restive northern Mali, the nation's UN mission said.READ: Mali extends state of emergency in bid to quell Islamist attacksThe troops were patrolling on foot near Aguelhok, which is close to the border with Algeria, when they were attacked, the mission said in a statement.A military source told AFP that the soldiers belonged to Chad's contingent.AFP